  "text": "where the spectral density ρ(s) is determined by a sum over the states of the theory (e.g. [CITATION_1] ) and ultraviolet subtractions is a polynomial in q 2 . The spectrum of the correlator in eq. (1), or the support of the function ρ(s) from eq. (2), is determined by singularities of the function Π(q 2 ) in the complex q 2 plane. The spectral density ρ(s) is then given by the discontinuity of the function Π(q 2 ) across the spectrum",
